<title>HONG KONG: Nam Pei Hong year net loss HK$23.13 mln.</title>
<headline>Nam Pei Hong year net loss HK$23.13 mln.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1996-08-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year ended March 31</p>
<p>(in million HK$ unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr (H.K. cents)	   14.9 loss  vs 2.2 gain (adjusted)</p>
<p>    Dividend (H.K. cents)    nil	  vs nil</p>
<p>    Exceptional items	  15.09 loss vs 2.30 loss</p>
<p>    Net			    23.13 loss vs 3.35 profit</p>
<p>    Turnover		     249.45     vs 173.32</p>
<p>    Company name		 Nam Pei Hong (Holdings) Ltd</p>
<p>    Books close		  N/A</p>
<p>    Dividend payable	   N/A</p>
<p>NOTE - A Chinese medicine and health food retailer and manufacturer.</p>
<p>Net is after an exceptional loss mainly on provision for diminution in value of the China joint ventures, doubtful debts, inventories and disposal of fixed assets upon closure of retail outlets.</p>
<p>Comparative share earnings adjusted for one-for-10 bonus share issue on August 31, 1995.</p>
<p>Total dividend for the year is nil vs nil.</p>
<p>-- Hong Kong Newsroom (852) 2843 6368</p>
